# Site feature visibility (private / hidden / shareable)

When the user says a feature is **private**, **hidden**, **not shown on the site**, **permalink-only**, **shareable** (link-only), or similar — update **`scripts/lib/site-feature-policy.mjs`** (`SITE_FEATURES`). Do not scatter regexes or path lists in other files.

## User says → you do

| User intent | `visibility` | Also wire |
|-------------|--------------|-----------|
| private / hidden permalink (like `/spreadsheet`, `/labfiles`) | `hidden` | `appPermalinks.js`, `artifactDownloads.js`, `App.jsx` download handler if new |
| shareable download link (like `/roles/...`) | `shareable` | same app wiring; `scrubKeywords` usually empty |
| valid route but not promoted (like `/env-vars`) | `semi-public` | SEO/sitemap as needed |
| normal explorer feature | `public` | sitemap if dialog |

## Registry entry template

```js
{
  id: "feature-id",
  visibility: "hidden",
  permalink: { segment: "feature-id" },
  siteUpdates: {
    commitKeywords: ["feature name", "/feature-id"],
    scrubKeywords: ["feature name", "/feature-id"],
    dataOnlyPaths: [
      /^public\/feature-templates\//,
      /^scripts\/generate-feature\.mjs$/,
    ],
  },
},
```

Infer `commitKeywords`, `scrubKeywords`, and `dataOnlyPaths` from the files you create or change (generators, `public/` output dirs, templates).

## Build consumers (read policy — do not duplicate)

- `scripts/lib/site-updates-generate.mjs` — site updates filter + scrub
- `scripts/write-sitemap.mjs` — `PUBLIC_SITEMAP_DIALOG_PATHS` only

After adding a hidden feature, no manual site-updates regex edits are needed. CI scrub runs automatically.

## Quick check

Hidden features must **not** appear in auto-generated `public/site-updates-data/`. If user asks to verify, run `npm run generate-site-updates -- --scrub`.
